n = int(input())
books = []
exers = []
exvals = set()
excount = {}
for _ in range(n):
    s = tuple(map(str, input().split()))
    if s[0] == '-1':
        minex = min(exvals)
        rem = 0
        bn = books.pop()
        ev = exers.pop()
        excount[ev] -= 1
        if excount[ev] == 0:
            exvals.remove(ev)
        while ev != minex:
            bn = books.pop()
            ev = exers.pop()
            excount[ev] -= 1
            if excount[ev] == 0:
                exvals.remove(ev)
            rem += 1
        print('{} {}'.format(rem, bn))
    elif int(s[0]) != 0:
        books.append(s[1])
        exers.append(int(s[0]))
        exvals.add(int(s[0]))
        if int(s[0]) in excount:
            excount[int(s[0])] += 1
        else:
            excount[int(s[0])] = 1

n = int(input())
names = []
rest = []
pref = []
size = 0
for tc in range(n):
    r_b = input().split()
    if len(r_b) == 1:
        t = pref[size - 1]
        prev = size - 1
        ind = size - 1
        while rest[ind] != t:
            rest.pop()
            names.pop()
            pref.pop()
            ind -= 1
            size -= 1
        name = names[ind]
        cnt = prev - ind
        rest.pop()
        names.pop()
        pref.pop()
        size -= 1
        print(str(cnt) + ' ' + name)
    else:
        r = int(r_b[0])
        b = r_b[1]
        if r == 0:
            continue
        names.append(b)
        rest.append(r)
        if size == 0:
            pref.append(r)
        else:
            pref.append(min(pref[size - 1], r))
        size += 1

from collections import deque as dq
n = int(input())
books = dq([])
record = dq([])
while n > 0:
    n -= 1
    line = str(input()).split(' ')
    k = int(line[0])
    if k == -1:
        print(str(record[0]['diff']) + ' ' + str(books.pop()))
        record.popleft()
    elif k > 0:
        name = line[1]
        if len(record) == 0 or k <= record[0]['ex_count']:
            record.appendleft({'ex_count': k, 'diff': 0})
            books.append(name)
        else:
            record[0]['diff'] += 1

while t:
    arr = list(input().split())

        minimum = min_stack[len(min_stack) - 1]
        count = 0
        while len(stack) > 0 and stack[len(stack) - 1][0] != minimum:
            x = stack.pop()
            count += 1
        print(count, stack[len(stack) - 1][1])
        stack.pop()
        min_stack.pop()
    elif int(arr[0]) > 0:
        if len(min_stack) == 0:
            min_stack.append(int(arr[0]))
        elif min_stack[len(min_stack) - 1] >= int(arr[0]):
